    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but healing what? there’s nothing to heal. you can’t fix a canvas that’s been burnt to ash. it’s not a \"phase\" or a \"dip\"... it’s just that the essence of me is gone. the music, the vision, the spark... it was the only thing that made being human worth the effort. without it, i’m just taking up space. just a biological machine going through the motions. it feels so pointless to keep forcing this thing to exist when the soul has already left.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
